-- Iraq Postpones Persian Gulf Oil Terminal Start “Indefinitely”
-- B y   K a d h i m   A j r a s h
-- 2012-01-25T11:54:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/iraq-postpones-persian-gulf-oil-terminal-start-indefinitely-.html
Iraq  has postponed “indefinitely”
the inauguration of the first of four single-point mooring
facilities in the  Persian Gulf , said Murtada al-Jashaami, a
spokesman for the oil ministry.  He didn’t give any reason for the delay, the third since
last month.  The government plans to install three more offshore loading
points by 2013, Oil Minister Abdul Kareem al-Luaibi said Jan.
18. Each mooring facility will add 850,000 barrels a day of
loading capacity, he said.  Iraq, which holds the world’s fifth-largest crude deposits,
according BP Plc data, wants to raise production and exports to
promote economic growth. It has granted 15 oil and gas licenses
since the U.S.-led invasion in 2003 and plans a new round on
April 11-12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
